                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9958: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Earle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-14T23:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 14, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 15—2:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>188. Heavy movement of Bulgarian troops by night through Sofia may mean
                    occupation of Thrace and Macedonia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Earle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
